[{"location":"api/#API-Reference","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#Discretization","page":"API Reference","title":"Discretization","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#HelmholtzBenchmark.discretize_helmholtz","page":"API Reference","title":"HelmholtzBenchmark.discretize_helmholtz","text":"discretize_helmholtz(n::Int, k::Real) -> (A::SparseMatrixCSC{Float64,Int}, b::Vector{Float64})\n\nDiscretize the Helmholtz equation (-²-k²)u = f on 01 using second-order finite differences. Uses n interior points (resulting in an n times n matrix). f is set to a delta function at x = 12. Returns the system matrix A and the right-hand side vector b.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#Solvers","page":"API Reference","title":"Solvers","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#HelmholtzBenchmark.solve_helmholtz_direct","page":"API Reference","title":"HelmholtzBenchmark.solve_helmholtz_direct","text":"solve_helmholtz_direct(A::AbstractMatrix, b::AbstractVector) -> Vector{Float64}\n\nSolve the Helmholtz system using the LinearSolve.jl interface to the UMFPACK direct solver.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#HelmholtzBenchmark.solve_helmholtz_iterative","page":"API Reference","title":"HelmholtzBenchmark.solve_helmholtz_iterative","text":"solve_helmholtz_iterative(A::AbstractMatrix, b::AbstractVector; \n                        tol::Real=1e-6, maxiter::Int=100) -> Vector{Float64}\n\nSolve the Helmholtz system using the LinearSolve.jl interface to the GMRES iterative solver provided by Krylov.jl.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#Benchmarking","page":"API Reference","title":"Benchmarking","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#HelmholtzBenchmark.run_benchmark","page":"API Reference","title":"HelmholtzBenchmark.run_benchmark","text":"run_benchmark(k_values::Vector{<:Real}, dim::Int = 1, n::Int = 100)\n\nCompare direct (UMFPACK) and iterative (GMRES) solvers for the Helmholtz equation for a number of wave numbers k_values.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#HelmholtzBenchmark.run_comparison","page":"API Reference","title":"HelmholtzBenchmark.run_comparison","text":"run_comparison(k::Real, dim::Int = 1, n::Int = 100)\n\nCompare direct (UMFPACK) and iterative (GMRES) solvers for the Helmholtz equation for a single wave number k.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#HelmholtzBenchmark.verify_solution","page":"API Reference","title":"HelmholtzBenchmark.verify_solution","text":"verify_solution()\n\nVerify the implementation by comparing with the exact solution for k=0 and f=1, where u(x) = (12)x(1-x).\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"changelog/#Changelog","page":"Changelog","title":"Changelog","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"changelog/#v0.1.0-August-5,-2025","page":"Changelog","title":"v0.1.0 August 5, 2025","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"changelog/","page":"Changelog","title":"Changelog","text":"initial commits including:\nsimple 1D toy problem setup\nbenchmark comparison between direct and iterative solvers\nverification of discretization using analytical solution for case k=0, fequiv 1.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"using Markdown\nMarkdown.parse(read(\"../../README.md\",String))","category":"page"}]
